s:8:\"registry\";r:1119;}s:9:\"useragent\";s:90:\"SimplePie/1.3.1 (Feed Parser; http://simplepie.org; Allow like Gecko) Build/20171007101814\";s:8:\"feed_url\";N;s:4:\"file\";N;s:8:\"raw_data\";s:18649:\"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?><rss version=\"2.0\"\n	xmlns:content=\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\"\n	xmlns:wfw=\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\"\n	xmlns:dc=\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\"\n	xmlns:atom=\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\"\n	xmlns:sy=\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\"\n	xmlns:slash=\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\"\n	>\n\n<channel>\n	<title>Blog &#8211; Timely</title>\n	<atom:link href=\"https://time.ly/blog/feed/\" rel=\"self\" type=\"application/rss+xml\" />\n	<link>https://time.ly</link>\n	<description>Website Calendar by Timely</description>\n	<lastBuildDate>Thu, 05 Oct 2017 11:30:48 +0000</lastBuildDate>\n	<language>en-US</language>\n	<sy:updatePeriod>hourly</sy:updatePeriod>\n	<sy:updateFrequency>1</sy:updateFrequency>\n	\n	<item>\n		<title>Latest Update To Our WordPress Plugin Addons</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/latest-update-wordpress-plugin-addons/</link>\n		<pubDate>Wed, 20 Sep 2017 13:08:56 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">https://time.ly/?p=326167</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>In our latest update, you may have noticed your WordPress Add-ons stopped working. To reactivate them simply sign into your Timely account via the settings page of your WordPress Core Calendar Plugin. We are adding functionality and making performance improvements to our addons that will provide more value to you. This involves running some components<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/latest-update-wordpress-plugin-addons/\" title=\"ReadLatest Update To Our WordPress Plugin Addons\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/latest-update-wordpress-plugin-addons/\">Latest Update To Our WordPress Plugin Addons</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Build Your Brand By White-labeling Your Calendar</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/build-brand-white-labeling-calendar/</link>\n		<pubDate>Thu, 24 Aug 2017 18:11:19 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">https://time.ly/?p=325737</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>With Timely&#8217;s latest release you can continue to push your brand out to the public. Available for Timely Pro, Timely Hublite and Timely Hub calendar subscriptions. What can you do? Hide the Timely Logo Add your logo to Timely Ticketing Add your logo to the Front End Submissions page Timely events calendar specializes in helping<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/build-brand-white-labeling-calendar/\" title=\"ReadBuild Your Brand By White-labeling Your Calendar\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/build-brand-white-labeling-calendar/\">Build Your Brand By White-labeling Your Calendar</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Automate Your Newsletters Through the Timely Hub Calendar</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/automate-newsletters-timely-hub-calendar/</link>\n		<pubDate>Fri, 04 Aug 2017 20:15:48 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">https://time.ly/?p=325430</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>Time.ly Hub calendars have a basic integration with MailChimp designed to make your life easier! You can automate the process of sending out daily, weekly or monthly event newsletters based on the events in your calendar. Additionally, you can use the Single Mail feature to send out custom email newsletters or notifications to specific subscribers. <a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/automate-newsletters-timely-hub-calendar/\" title=\"ReadAutomate Your Newsletters Through the Timely Hub Calendar\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/automate-newsletters-timely-hub-calendar/\">Automate Your Newsletters Through the Timely Hub Calendar</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Improve Seo on your Timely Website Calendar By Creating a Custom Domain</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/improve-seo-timely-website-calendar-creating-custom-domain/</link>\n		<pubDate>Tue, 18 Jul 2017 18:57:03 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">https://time.ly/?p=325261</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>With the Timely Pro, Timely Hublite and Timely Hub Calendar you can create a custom domain for your calendar which will help improve your SEO (search engine optimization)!  Normally you would embed the widget code onto your webpage. Now you can simply link to your custom sub-domain (e.g. events.mydomain) all of the event url&#8217;s will<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/improve-seo-timely-website-calendar-creating-custom-domain/\" title=\"ReadImprove Seo on your Timely Website Calendar By Creating a Custom Domain\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/improve-seo-timely-website-calendar-creating-custom-domain/\">Improve Seo on your Timely Website Calendar By Creating a Custom Domain</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>How To Leverage The Timely Website Calendar Network</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/leverage-timelys-website-calendar-network/</link>\n		<pubDate>Thu, 29 Jun 2017 18:08:01 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">https://time.ly/?p=325055</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>Hub and Hublite events calendar owners can allow members in their community to send events directly to their site using a couple of methods. Enable Front end Submissions. Having Timely Free and Timely Pro calendars sync their events via .ics feed. They can click here to sign up! The second option greatly simplifies the process,<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/leverage-timelys-website-calendar-network/\" title=\"ReadHow To Leverage The Timely Website Calendar Network\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/leverage-timelys-website-calendar-network/\">How To Leverage The Timely Website Calendar Network</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Website Calendars For Schools</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/website-calendars-schools/</link>\n		<pubDate>Thu, 08 Jun 2017 15:49:45 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">https://time.ly/?p=324810</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>Timely Events Calendar is a great solution for schools.  Our website calendar provides a simple way of promoting events to the community, parents, teachers and students. Paper Newsletters are getting old, and usually don&#8217;t make it home. A school can easily embed the calendar onto their website or use it as a standalone page. Create<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/website-calendars-schools/\" title=\"ReadWebsite Calendars For Schools\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/website-calendars-schools/\">Website Calendars For Schools</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>I have a Core Calendar But I Need More</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/core-calendar-need/</link>\n		<pubDate>Fri, 26 May 2017 19:49:38 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">https://time.ly/?p=324609</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>You have the Timely Core calendar and you are looking for a little bit more? With the Core+ you will have 5 additional great add-ons which will help you continue to create a beautiful calendar. Extended Views: create a more visually appealing calendar which will help attract visitors to your site with the Posterboard and<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/core-calendar-need/\" title=\"ReadI have a Core Calendar But I Need More\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/core-calendar-need/\">I have a Core Calendar But I Need More</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Timely Ticketing &#038; Event Registration &#8211; The Simple Solution</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/timely-ticketing-event-registration-simple-solution/</link>\n		<pubDate>Fri, 12 May 2017 18:53:25 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">https://time.ly/?p=324526</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>Timely Low Cost Ticketing Solution Timely provides a low cost ticketing solution which is great if you have simple ticketing needs. For $59.00 a year you can create as many tickets as you like. Use a solution that will also be your marketing tool Timely tickets is used in conjunction with our events calendar. You<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/timely-ticketing-event-registration-simple-solution/\" title=\"ReadTimely Ticketing &#038; Event Registration &#8211; The Simple Solution\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/timely-ticketing-event-registration-simple-solution/\">Timely Ticketing &#038; Event Registration &#8211; The Simple Solution</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>How To Monetize Your Calendar &#8211; Timely Hub</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/monetize-calendar-timely-hub-calendar/</link>\n		<pubDate>Wed, 03 May 2017 19:16:59 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">https://time.ly/?p=324446</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>Here are two great ways you can monetize your calendar 1. Charge via the Post Your Event button (Hub) You are providing the service of promotion. People are spending their time to post events to your site. Furthermore, it is the perfect time to ask them to pay for additional services to get their event<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/monetize-calendar-timely-hub-calendar/\" title=\"ReadHow To Monetize Your Calendar &#8211; Timely Hub\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/monetize-calendar-timely-hub-calendar/\">How To Monetize Your Calendar &#8211; Timely Hub</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Import Feed Changes to Timely Core Calendars</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/import-feed-changes-timely-core-calendars/</link>\n		<pubDate>Fri, 21 Apr 2017 18:43:48 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">https://time.ly/?p=324307</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>We&#8217;re taking the ability to import feeds &#38; connecting calendars to a new level.   In the past we&#8217;ve offered the ability to import feeds as a free service. Going forward, we&#8217;re asking you to support us so that we can better support you and the community you serve. The Core will only come with<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/import-feed-changes-timely-core-calendars/\" title=\"ReadImport Feed Changes to Timely Core Calendars\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/import-feed-changes-timely-core-calendars/\">Import Feed Changes to Timely Core Calendars</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Build Up Your Network &#8211; Timely Hub Calendar</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/build-network-timely-hub-calendar/</link>\n		<pubDate>Mon, 03 Apr 2017 19:19:34 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">https://time.ly/?p=323932</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>You have a great looking calendar and now you need to build up your network. Here are some tips on how to do so. Use Landing Pages Create a page which tells venues/sources how to send events form their calendar to yours. 2. Auto -responses from front-end Submissions Anyone who has taken the time to<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/build-network-timely-hub-calendar/\" title=\"ReadBuild Up Your Network &#8211; Timely Hub Calendar\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/build-network-timely-hub-calendar/\">Build Up Your Network &#8211; Timely Hub Calendar</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Latest Release Notes</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/latest-release-notes-2/</link>\n		<pubDate>Fri, 24 Mar 2017 13:11:34 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">https://time.ly/?p=323797</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>Released Mar 27, 2017 Here the fixes we have made in our latest release. Fixed: Returned the missing label for the previous month button (month view). Fixed: Improved the handling of missing or poorly formatted timezones when importing events. Fixed: Plugin wasn’t enabling certain features in the WP Multisite Environment. Fixed: An undefined index error would<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/latest-release-notes-2/\" title=\"ReadLatest Release Notes\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/latest-release-notes-2/\">Latest Release Notes</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Promotional Services Through Your Timely Hub Calendar</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/promotional-services-timely-hub-calendar/</link>\n		<pubDate>Thu, 16 Mar 2017 15:00:28 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">https://time.ly/?p=323725</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>Becoming the Hub of your community sometimes means promoting a business or their events. Here are a few ways you can promote a business and their events. With a Timely Hub calendar you can allow businesses to post events via your front end submissions form.   Featured events (Hub) You can embed featured events either above your main<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/promotional-services-timely-hub-calendar/\" title=\"ReadPromotional Services Through Your Timely Hub Calendar\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/promotional-services-timely-hub-calendar/\">Promotional Services Through Your Timely Hub Calendar</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Latest Release Notes</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/latest-release-notes/</link>\n		<pubDate>Fri, 10 Mar 2017 14:42:19 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">https://time.ly/?p=323697</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>Check out a list of our latest improvements &#38; fixes. Released Mar 9, 2017 Fixed: Open Graph meta tags now matches correct dates and URLs for recurrent events. Fixed: Prevents duplicate post IDs from being passed to update_meta_cache() after searching for events, creating a much smaller database query. Thanks to @zrothauser for the fix. Fixed: Removed<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/latest-release-notes/\" title=\"ReadLatest Release Notes\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/latest-release-notes/\">Latest Release Notes</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Become Your Community Thought Leader</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/become-community-thought-leader/</link>\n		<pubDate>Fri, 03 Mar 2017 21:03:00 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">https://time.ly/?p=323633</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>Timely pushes the boundaries on our oldest social technology &#8211; Calendars. Calendars have always been around helping to organize people&#8217;s schedules and events. It is hard to find someone who does not have any form of a calendar as they are still very relevant in our society. Today almost all events are found online. With<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/become-community-thought-leader/\" title=\"ReadBecome Your Community Thought Leader\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/become-community-thought-leader/\">Become Your Community Thought Leader</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>API 0.7.0 Release Notes</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/api-0-7-0-release-notes/</link>\n		<pubDate>Fri, 17 Feb 2017 19:13:13 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">https://time.ly/?p=323400</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>Release Notes Web Application: 1. To save you time, view, clone and trash options have been added to quick edits. You no longer have to make these changes by going into the all events page. 2. Receive the latest style and javascript updates instantly.  No more waiting for caches to clear. 3. Display your calendar beautifully<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/api-0-7-0-release-notes/\" title=\"ReadAPI 0.7.0 Release Notes\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/api-0-7-0-release-notes/\">API 0.7.0 Release Notes</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n	</channel>\n</rss>\n\";s:7:\"timeout\";i:10;s:15:\"force_fsockopen\";b:0;s:10:\"force_feed\";b:0;s:5:\"cache\";b:1;s:14:\"cache_duration\";i:3600;s:28:\"autodiscovery_cache_duration\";i:604800;s:14:\"cache_location\";s:7:\"./cache\";s:19:\"cache_name_function\";s:3:\"md5\";s:13:\"order_by_date\";b:1;s:14:\"input_encoding\";b:0;s:13:\"autodiscovery\";i:31;s:8:\"registry\";r:1119;s:17:\"max_checked_feeds\";i:10;s:20:\"all_discovered_feeds\";a:0:{}s:13:\"image_handler\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"multifeed_url\";a:0:{}s:17:\"multifeed_objects\";a:0:{}s:15:\"config_settings\";N;s:10:\"item_limit\";i:0;s:16:\"strip_attributes\";a:14:{i:0;s:7:\"bgsound\";i:1;s:5:\"class\";i:2;s:4:\"expr\";i:3;s:2