(24, 1, '2017-09-15 14:26:49', '2017-09-15 12:26:49', '<img class=\"wp-image-430 alignleft\" style=\"float:left; width:45%; margin-right: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px;\" src=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/wEczM9hP_400x400-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"245\" height=\"245\" />\r\n<h2>The spread and evolutions of information technologies and digital tools have enabled an entire new dimension of big-data</h2>\r\nand analytics that can bring tremendous improvements accros industries, including healthcare. This paper recommends the creation of a European wide connected Electronic Health Records Organisation (EHRD) empowering patients by enabling the effective collection and usage of patients by enabling the effective collection revolutionising healthcare and ultimately leading to better health outcomes for patients and prayers irrespective of national borders.', '1st Edition 2015', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1rst-edition-2015', '', '', '2017-10-10 22:45:46', '2017-10-10 20:45:46', '', 0, 'http://4883dc5101.url-de-test.ws/?page_id=24', 0, 'page', '', 0),
