(486, 1, '2017-09-29 09:47:30', '2017-09-29 07:47:30', 'The European Health Parliament (EHP) is a platform of 55 young professionals/students from across Europe, who are working together over 7 months, with the aim of shaping the future of healthcare in Europe. Throughout this time, participants are working and brainstorming in 5 committees around specific topics ranging from digital skills for the medical profession, prevention & self-care, antimicrobial resistance and others. They meet with key stakeholders and share their ideas with policymakers, NGOs, media and the interested general public in order to deliver high-level policy-oriented recommendations to be presented to the European Commission as possible legislative proposals. The project takes place in Brussels.', 'Partners', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '4-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-09-29 09:47:30', '2017-09-29 07:47:30', '', 4, 'http://4883dc5101.url-de-test.ws/4-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
