(507, 1, '2017-10-05 11:17:12', '2017-10-05 09:17:12', '<div class=\"bp bp-loaded box-show-preview-controls\">\r\n<div class=\"bp-doc bp-doc-document bp-is-scrollable\">\r\n<div class=\"pdfViewer\">\r\n<div id=\"bp-page-1\" class=\"page\" data-page-number=\"1\" data-loaded=\"true\">\r\n<div class=\"textLayer\">\r\n<h3>1. What is the overall objective of the European Health Parliament?</h3>\r\n<div>The 6 initiating partners aspire to create &amp; facilitate an idea-generating platform with 55 young professionals and students who want to help shape the outlook of future European healthcare. The 55 participants will form a European Health Parliament (EHP) and formulate innovative ideas for making Europe a healthier place and reshaping the European healthcare system. The ideas will be shared with policy makers and the healthcare community across the EU Member States.</div>\r\n<h3>2. Who can participate?</h3>\r\n<div>We are looking for enthusiastic young thinkers with an ambition to co-shape future Europe and to co-author policy recommendations. Participants need to be below 35 years old and hold at least a Bachelor degree. Prior experience or background in healthcare is desired, but not required.</div>\r\n<h3>3. What are the timelines?</h3>\r\n<div>The Third Edition of the EHP lasts for 7 months. A kick-off meeting has been organized on the 3rd of October at the Radisson Red, Rue d\'Idalie 35, 1050 Ixelles, Belgium. This is just an informal after work cocktail.</div>\r\n<div>4 Plenary sessions (1-day meeting) have been scheduled in the course of the program. They will take place in the Brussels area on the following dates:</div>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>October 17th 2017 (Opening Session)</li>\r\n 	<li>December 05th 2017</li>\r\n 	<li>February 20th 2018</li>\r\n 	<li>April 24th 2018 (Closing Session)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<div>Participants\' availability is required at all Plenary Sessions.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>4. How will the European Health Parliament work in practice?</h3>\r\n<div>During the first kick-off meeting, partners present the list of 5 themes/topics so that participants have 2 weeks to decide on which one to be engaged. EHP participants will be then divided into 5 Committees according to their preferences. Topics will be disclosed soon.</div>\r\n<div>At the 1st Plenary Session:</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>participants elect their own EHP President;</li>\r\n 	<li>each Committee will elect a Committee Chairperson. The elected EHP President and the elected 5 EHP Committee Chairpersons are added to the Steering Committee as from October 2017 onwards. The Committees will determine independently their own internal processes and working modus. The 6 initiating Partners will provide logistic, methodological and editorial support if requested by the Committee.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>Then each EHP Committee begins working around 1 specific theme/topic, which will result in a policy recommendation at the end of the program. The Committees will communicate their ideas via several social media channels throughout the program.</div>\r\n<h3>5. How much time should I dedicate to this project?</h3>\r\n<div>Participants are required to be available and engage actively in the 4 Plenary Sessions. In between sessions, it is up to each Committee to identify the most suitable working method. Committee participants can meet face-to-face and/or communicate via a wide range of social media and platforms that will be at their disposal.</div>\r\n<h3>6. What is the cost for participants?</h3>\r\n<div>There is no participation fee for participants. Travel/logistics costs will not be reimbursed.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>7. More questions?</h3>\r\n<div>For more information, please contact us via e-mail contact@healthparliament.eu</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"bp-controls-wrapper\"></div>', 'FAQ', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '10-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-05 11:17:12', '2017-10-05 09:17:12', '', 10, 'http://4883dc5101.url-de-test.ws